ARC boat measurement at Horsefly River Flats Rec Site. Section seemed good a bit of turbulence mid-channel but manageable. First solo RC boat measurement had difficulty holding boat steady on far edge and using rangefinder. Did not include first 2 transects as the boat track/edge holding was not great and they plotted lower and higher than the following transects. End of oline found buried in silt on arrival. SRC should be applied to bring the low end of HG values in line with DWL. Moved anchor deeper at 12:07pst under about 1.1m of water landed on a rock hopefully less prone to silting. Reset HG to 5.748m at 12:19pst. Values above 6m can be removed. ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy  Light Rain  Calm Wind
column14: MGH ADJUSTED TO DWL SINCE SENSOR WAS DISCOVERED TO BE MALFUNCTIONING AFTER VISIT.  ARC boat measurement at Horsefly River Flats Rec Site 3km upstream of gauge. Flow was a bit turbulent on left half of channel but we were able to measure at the end of the path to the river and slightly upstream. Throttle was near maxed out in thalweg and the remote was beeping at us for this. Wouldn't measure much higher with ARC boat here. Rat creek measurement site was too turbulent. ARC measurement at gauge looks possible but a big effort to carry boat down from road. Reset HG to 6.481m at 12:37pst. Measured handful of high water marks - silt deposits and fine debris (needles). No really clear high water marks taken just to give an idea. Water had been above lower path to station. MGH calculated from time-weighted logger readings in excel spreadsheet "08KH031_2020_MGH_calculations.xlsx" in computation folder on server. Assume SRC when line was pulled out is constant from last visit (should be 0 or close to it). SRC after reset is within surge do not apply SRC going forward. ADCP by Moving Boat
